WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:29.800
Hi, Grandpa. Hi, ready? Can I help? Yes, indeed.

00:30.800 --> 00:33.800
Hand me two eggs from the refrigerator.

00:33.800 --> 00:36.800
And I'll make you two fried eggs.

00:37.800 --> 00:42.800
How about some bacon? Well, I've made enough for an army.

00:42.800 --> 00:45.800
You're going to the baseball game today?

00:45.800 --> 00:47.800
It's a perfect day for it.

00:47.800 --> 00:50.800
A little crowded, but nice and warm.

00:50.800 --> 00:53.800
Dad and I were planning to go to the game, but he has to work today.

00:53.800 --> 00:55.800
And my friends don't want to go.

00:55.800 --> 00:57.800
It's not an important game anyway.

00:58.800 --> 01:00.800
Do you have any other plans for the day?

01:00.800 --> 01:02.800
Well, I'll work on my computer.

01:02.800 --> 01:05.800
I have a new math program and I want to learn how to use it.

01:05.800 --> 01:09.800
Maybe you can teach me how to work on a computer someday.

01:09.800 --> 01:14.800
Anytime. It's really easy, but like anything you need to work at, Grandpa.

01:14.800 --> 01:16.800
Hmm.

01:16.800 --> 01:20.800
The bacon is great. I love crispy bacon.

01:21.800 --> 01:23.800
Oh, what are you doing tomorrow?

01:23.800 --> 01:25.800
Nothing much.

01:26.800 --> 01:31.800
Well, maybe your dad and I could take you fishing with us.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.800
I'd like that, but...

01:33.800 --> 01:35.800
But... what?

01:35.800 --> 01:37.800
But Dad is always so busy.

01:37.800 --> 01:42.800
Well, can you come fishing with me tomorrow?

01:43.800 --> 01:45.800
Sure I can.

01:47.800 --> 01:50.800
Robbie says you can't take him to the game today.

01:50.800 --> 01:54.800
I really feel bad about it, but they need me at the hospital day in the children's ward.

01:55.800 --> 01:57.800
I understand.

01:57.800 --> 02:00.800
Maybe we can spend some time together next weekend.

02:00.800 --> 02:02.800
Definitely. We should.

02:02.800 --> 02:05.800
You and Robbie and me.

02:05.800 --> 02:08.800
Remember our first fishing trip?

02:08.800 --> 02:10.800
I sure do.

02:10.800 --> 02:13.800
Well, I've got to run, Dad.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.800
See you later.

02:15.800 --> 02:16.800
Oh.

02:16.800 --> 02:18.800
Well, fishing?

02:18.800 --> 02:20.800
I'm thinking about it.

02:20.800 --> 02:23.800
Oh, I was working.

02:23.800 --> 02:26.800
Oh, the usual problems.

02:26.800 --> 02:28.800
You're working pretty hard these days.

02:28.800 --> 02:30.800
I guess I am.

02:33.800 --> 02:36.800
When did you last go fishing with Robbie?

02:36.800 --> 02:38.800
I remember exactly.

02:38.800 --> 02:42.800
It was my first day, June 2nd, two years ago.

02:42.800 --> 02:45.800
We didn't catch anything.

02:45.800 --> 02:49.800
Remember our fishing trips?

02:49.800 --> 02:51.800
Yes.

02:51.800 --> 02:53.800
I loved them.

02:53.800 --> 02:57.800
Remember catching your first fish?

02:57.800 --> 03:01.800
I'll get them for getting fell out of the boat.

03:01.800 --> 03:06.800
We had some good times together.

03:06.800 --> 03:09.800
Yes, we did.

03:09.800 --> 03:12.800
Maybe we should do it again.

03:12.800 --> 03:14.800
About tomorrow.

03:14.800 --> 03:16.800
Don't you have to work?

03:16.800 --> 03:19.800
My paperwork will wait.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.800
Robbie will be thrilled.

03:21.800 --> 03:22.800
I am too, son.

03:22.800 --> 03:24.800
I'm going to spend more time with Robbie.

03:24.800 --> 03:26.800
Tomorrow.

03:26.800 --> 03:29.800
It'll be like old times for you and me.

03:29.800 --> 03:31.800
And Robbie will love it.

03:31.800 --> 03:35.800
Well, what's the weather going to be like?

03:35.800 --> 03:38.800
Radio says, sonny and mild.

03:38.800 --> 03:40.800
Oh.

03:40.800 --> 03:42.800
Well, it's a good weather.

03:42.800 --> 03:47.800
Well, I'll tell Robbie.

03:47.800 --> 03:51.800
And thanks, Dad.

03:51.800 --> 03:53.800
Don't thank me.

03:53.800 --> 03:56.800
I'm just being a grandfather.

03:56.800 --> 03:58.800
Thank you.

